The State files an Amended Information which amends the charge to misdemeanor PTC retail theft, contrary to Sections 943.50(1m)(b) and 939.05 of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment counseling as deemed appropriate  by the Departments assessment process;
2)  AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Spend fifteen (15) days, under the Huber Law, commencing on 11-20-14 by 5:00 p.m.  Court authorizes transfer to Brown County Jail;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) maintain absolute sobriety.
Amended Information.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Victim Impact Statement.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. 
Minutes.
